Taiwan December offshore banking unit assets rise . The combined assets of Taiwan ' s 65 offshore banking units grew 9 . 0 percent to a new high of US $ 36 . 59 billion at the end of December from a year earlier , the central bank said on Monday . About 77 percent of the assets , held by 36 local banks and 29 foreign banks , came from Asia and the rest from Europe and America , the bank said in a statement . The statement added that the bank had recently approved four more offshore banking unit applications by foreign banks and one more by a local bank . In December , Taiwan ' s offshore banking units reported a monthly foreign exchange turnover of $ 3 . 742 billion , the statement said . Of the derivatives operated by theese units , margin trading accounted for $ 403 million , options $ 282 million , financial futures accounted for $ 72 million , interest rate swaps took $ 51 million and forward interest rate agreements took $ 5 million . The government has planned to expand the offshore banking unit business as part of its scheme to become a regional financial centre . This expansion would herald some tax burden for these units , although its size is still unspecified , officials have said . 
